Almost time for wine! I got through my supermarket trip earlier..just.  I decided rather than walking to our local one as I have done for 6 weeks, I would take my car to a bigger one to have more choice and be able to get more but it was awful. It was pretty quick to get in but once I was inside, it was way too busy which made it impossible to keep apart from the supermarket staff let alone the other people. I actually felt very anxious to be around so many people and I spent a fortune. I won't be doing that again but at least we will be very well stocked for a while. I even treated myself to these flowers. 
This afternoon I managed to move the ladders on the bunk beds by myself (with actual tools and stuff) so the room is finally finished. The Star Wars sheets arrived too so they have been washed and tumbled, ready for using tonight. The sheets are pretty bright and not very insta friendly but my boys really love them and that is the important thing. This afternoon we are hunkered down watching a film. It has been a long week but happy that we are all happy, safe and well. I hope you are too?

But too often people believe the opposite. They believe in (or have experienced) a love that is conditional.

This is what i am experiencing from past few years. Parents are expecting so much from their children. In this fake and socially accepted world, parents usually say : .
•”I will love you if you make me feel like I’m a good parent.”
•”I will love you if you get good grades.”
•”I will love you if you look a certain way.”
.
This conditional love speaks more about the person giving it than the person it’s directed to. Love isn’t a merit system where only the super star students deserve the reward. Love is love is love.

Have you ever felt like your heart has been on God’s surgical table? And moreso now...where it seems like your thoughts and emotions have finally caught up with you...?
•
•
Have you found it easy to avoid the worries, the hurts, the pains, the wounds, the bruises of your heart, through the busyness of life...But that escape place of “busyness” doesn’t seem to be at bay now? And you’re finally confronted with the rawness of your heart with nowhere to hide...and it seems each day God is surfacing the compiled and hidden things you never wanted to admit to or face as you knew the pain would be too much to face?
•
•
What of if God told you, you’re in safe hands; His hands...And what you thought didn’t matter (but caused great hurt, worry, anxiety, grief and defence to your heart) is actually what He cares about most, more than the ‘works of your hands’...and He wants to have a time of openness and intimacy to discuss these things with you?
•
•
What of if the things you thought He didn’t care about are actually the things He cares most about. Allow Him in.

📷 Además, esta foto concretamente (al igual que lo serán las de esta columna), la hice nada más salir de lavarme el pelo.
🐜 Quien quiere, puede y quien no, pone excusas.

✴️ In life some people make excuses, others strive even if it costs more.
🖤 And this can apply to everything, from studies to the "simple" fact of staying at home and giving up seeing the ones you love the most these days.
📱This collection, for example, is made wearing a pyjamas (this seasonal outfit) with the front camera of my mobile phone and a small light source.
📷 In addition, this photo (just like all of this column) was taken when I had finished washing my hair.
🐜 When you really want something, you find a way. When you don't, you find an excuse.

امروز میخوام از روزای خوشمون یاد کنیم.
از رکوردامون💪،از درد لذت بخش بعد از تمرین🤕، از گوپ 👊گوپ👊 نبض مون موقع #لیفت و #اسکوات و #لانگز زدنمون🏋😅
چی میشه که دلتنگ یه مکان یا بهتره بگم یه فضا میشیم؟
مثلا دلتنگ خونه قدیمی مون،دلتنگ مدرسه و دانشگاهی که فارغ التحصیل شدیم...
این روزا مسئله ی #اعتیاد شدید #ورزشکاران به #ورزش و #باشگاه ها به همه ثابت شد...😥 یه جفت دمبل و یه کش هم این روزای #قرنطینه کارمو راه انداختن...
میدونی از چی حرف میزنم ؟ از روزایی که حالمون خوب بود ولی خب نمیدونستیم برا چی؟

من اون روز، موقع این عکس حالم خیلی خوب بود چون اون روز، آخرین سانس باشگاه توی سال۹۷ بود که فقط من و مربیم و یکی دونفر دیگه توی باشگاه به اون بزرگی بودیم.
چون برق چشمای #مربی ام منو شارژ میکرد ست آخرو سنگین تر بزنم 💪چون وقتی ازش تشکر میکردم با ذوق میگفت همش کار خودت بوده دختر 👌
تو بودی که یکسال و نیم تمام جون کندی که الان میتونی فلان کیلو لیفت بزنی...👊 شما یادتون میاد روزای خوب تون رو🤔؟ اگه راست میگین واسه چی حالتون خوب بوده؟؟؟😉😁
(تقلب:شاید اون روز عروس بودین،شاید یه شماره تلفن خیلی قشنگ روی صفحه گوشیتون افتاده،شاید اون روز بابا شدین،شاید دست مامانتونو بوسیدین،شاید بلایی ازتون دفع شده،شاید...)
دیگه بقیه شو خودتون توی کامنت بنویسید همین الان کدوم خاطره از روزای خوبتون یادتون اومد😍؟؟؟تازشم میتونید دوستاتون رو تگ کنید بیشتر خاطره بازی کنید 😋😄
پی نوشت:از این به بعد قدر روزای خوشحالیمون و دلیل های ساده اش رو بیشتر میدونیم...😌 ررررااااااستیییی اگر گفتید موزیکی که روی پست هست از کدوم پادکست آقای جهرمیه؟؟؟اسمش رو کامنت کنید تا بقیه دوستامون هم برن گوش کنند حسابی انرژی و انگیزه بگیرن✌😀💪

Puré de Camote

Ingredientes:
2 camotes
Sal gruesa
Pimienta negra y/o cajún
1 ramito de apio picada
1 cda de ajo picado
1 cdta de jengibre rayado
1/2 taza de cebolla blanca picada finita
1 rábano picado bien finito
1/2 taza de pimentones de colores picados bien finos
Aceite de coco
1/4 cdta de oregano, cardamomo , tomillo y perejil.

Procedimiento:
1. Lavar bien los camotes , quitar la cáscara y cortar en cuadrados. Poner a hervir con agua hasta que se cubran los camotes.
Para saber que están listos pinchalos con un tenedor y deben estar blandos.
2. En una sartén colocar los vegetales, sal y pimienta al gusto, las hierbas sazonadoras, jengibre junto con 3 cdas de aceite coco y poner a sofreir.
Hasta por 10 minutos.
Puedes agregar 3 cdas mas de aceite de coco si sientes que se secan loa vegetales.
3. Listos los camotes, pasar con un cucharón a un recipiente hondo donde puedas majarlos. Usa el agua que sobró de los camotes para ir haciendo el puré.
Si gustas puedes agregar leche vegetal.o la de tu preferencia.
4. Finalizado el puré servir en un recipiente y colocar encima la capa de sofrito.

QUARANTINE SKINCARE: 1 tbsp brown sugar, 1 tspn lime juice, 2 tbsp honey 
Although we should all be social distancing and not offering kisses to anyone at this time, it’s important that we don’t neglect our lips. Let’s keep them soft and smooth. By now I’m sure you know just how much I love a good ole DIY. So here’s a lip scrub DIY to keep those lips soft, smooth and hydrated.

Mix together all the ingredients. Next be sure to wash your hands (it’s quarantine season so we have to do our due diligence). After you wash your hands apply mixture to lips using your finger or a toothbrush. Be sure scrub top and bottom lip 4 to 5 times then let sit for 4 to 5 minutes before wiping off with a warm cloth or paper towel. 
BONUS: mix olive oil or avocado oil with honey to create a moisturizing lip balm!

Hobbs & Shaw 🍿
-
✨Lo bonito: Tiene mucha acción y escenas de pelea. El humor simple y rápido entre la Roca y Jason Statham se mantiene durante toda la película. La aparición de Ryan Reynolds con el humor característico de...Ryan Reynolds.
-
🌚Lo no tan bonito: A mí parecer, en estas películas uno busca harta acción, a veces humor, buenas peleas y un villano "simple". En este caso, el malo es muy existencial y oootra vez se busca aniquilar al % más débil de la humanidad, mediante una especie de Terminator. Fue mucho para una trama que podía haber sido mucho más simple y con ello mucho mejor 🤷🏻‍♀️
-
+ cosas no bonitas: Es más larga de lo necesario, en algunas tomas de cerca se notaba que los efectos especiales no fueron hechos con mucho cariño, de autos no tiene nada, hay un par de incoherencias muy obvias a lo largo de la película, así como escenas muy ridículas.
-
En resumen: No es mala, pero tiene muchas pifias y se complica demasiado a sí misma.

Lejos de sus hijos, madres de su familia, saliendo de casa muy temprano con temor y estres de enfrentar a este virus y a la sociedad. Hoy rezo más que nunca por ellas, por los medicos, por las que estan en los crematorios, por las que están en extremo riesgo de contagio, por las que están contagiadas luchando por su vida en  el hospital, por las que ya no están. finally sharing the recipe for these beauties with ya! mother’s day calls for a batch of my moms favorite energy balls! in case you didn’t know, we go through a batch of balls a day during the weekdays (and as always, a third is made with walnuts added in and 2/3 with chocolate chips) 🤪 this mother’s day I’m grateful to have 2 amazing mothers in my life to be quarantined with and sunny weather 🥰  what are you doing with your loved ones today? 👇🏼⁣
⁣
Happy Mother’s Day to all the moms, stepmoms, and grandmothers! ⁣
⁣
𝐀𝐏𝐏𝐋𝐄 𝐎𝐀𝐓 𝐁𝐀𝐋𝐋𝐒 ⁣
• 2 cup rolled oats⁣
• 1 cup grated apple ⁣
• 1/2 cup mixed nut butter (cotsco brand is my favorite but could do any you want!)⁣
• 1/4 cup ground flaxseed ⁣
• 1/3 cup maple syrup (or honey)⁣
• 1 tsp vanilla⁣
• as little or much cinnamon as ya like⁣
• pinch of salt⁣
• add ins -I did walnuts and dark choco chips ⁣
⁣
1) Add dry ingredients in one bowl (oats, flaxseed, cinnamon)⁣
2) Add wet ingredients in one bowl (everything else) ⁣
3) Fold together and then add whatever you want, roll into balls, store in fridge, and ENJOY⁣

Fortunately, hubs then added water (based on feel and texture of the dough), which resulted in a drier but easier to handle dough baby. With each bulk fermentation, the dough became more firm and airy (but not as hydrated and sticky as the previous bakes). End result: delicious, full, airy and soft #sourdough with crackling, crunchy exteriors. Have to work on timing next time, so we aren’t up until 10 pm. .
.

Growing up, this was one of my favorite dinners that my mom made and still is! ♥️ In honor of Mother’s Day, sharing this easy ROASTED TOMATO & GARLIC PASTA.

HOW TO MAKE:
1/2 box pasta
2 pints of tomatoes 
3 cloves garlic
2 T. olive oil 
1/2 c. basil, chopped
S/P

Add tomatoes and whole garlic (still in wrapper, not peeled) to a glass baking dish or sheet pan. Toss with olive oil and S/P. Bake on 375 F for 25-30 minutes until tomatoes are blistered. While tomatoes are roasting, cook pasta according to box.

Once tomatoes are completely soft and blistered. Remove from oven. Peel garlic and smash. Toss tomato mixture with pasta. Top with basil.
